item.title: Deconvolution and Image Segmentation
item.description: Group members: Johannes Hoseth, Sergiu Ropota, Katharina Granberg Deconvolution - A Way Of Increasing Output Size Within the field of computer vision, a well-known and multi-faceted area is segmentation, i.e. identifying and classifying objects in an image, via classes.
